Music settings is handeled in a proper config file and the relative volume of music files should be configurable.
We need a music handler, that takes care that any changes to different music files is handeled smoothly. If at any time music stops playing in the game or the music file is changed, fade out the just playing file (3 seconds fade / configurable). The new music file starts at full volume.
Loop all music files as long as no other file is started actively (except in-game playlist tracks which play once and auto-advance).

On the main menu (splash screen), play rebel_theme.mp3
In game play the 12 in-game tracks (in_game_1.mp3 … in_game_12.mp3) in shuffled random order. When a track finishes, crossfade to the next. After all 12 have played, reshuffle and continue.

On rebel capital ship destroyed play for 1 minute: imperial_march.mp3, then transition back to the shuffled playlist.
On imperial capital ship destroyed play for 1 minute: rebel_theme, then transition back to the shuffled playlist.

On Imperial victory (in game summary screen) play imperial_march.mp3
On Rebel victory (in game summary screen) play rebel_theme.mp3
